409
00:49:46,219 --> 00:50:01,219
Well, I would say when he was physically at the Institute, he of course was not treating patients in Scotland, but he was continuing to collect and analyze data from those cancer cases in Scotland.

410
00:50:01,219 --> 00:50:14,219
And continuing to work with people who were doing that for him in Scotland, developing ways of analyzing the data, automated data collection programs and things of that nature.

411
00:50:14,219 --> 00:50:27,219
So he was very involved in that while he was at the Institute. He also became increasingly involved in what today is called outreach or public education.

412
00:50:27,219 --> 00:50:40,219
And as the work with Cameron and Pauline on vitamin C in cancer became more well known, there were many queries from the public, particularly patients afflicted with cancer who wanted advice.

413
00:50:40,219 --> 00:50:45,219
How much vitamin C should I take? Where can I go to get it and so on and so forth?

414
00:50:45,219 --> 00:50:57,219
